- Aren't you cold?
- No, I'm well-built.

62
00:05:24,266 --> 00:05:26,146
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

63
00:05:41,826 --> 00:05:43,547
It's already 2:00. Let me walk you back.

64
00:05:49,226 --> 00:05:49,826
Okay.

65
00:05:51,826 --> 00:05:53,586
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

66
00:05:55,346 --> 00:05:58,786
I'll walk you back and then walk around.

67
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:00,947
Aren't you sleepy?

68
00:06:03,067 --> 00:06:05,067
I forgot to tell you.

69
00:06:06,107 --> 00:06:07,307
Mr. Mo

70
00:06:08,346 --> 00:06:11,280
sent me a message that
Sheng fell asleep in my room

71
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,547
and told me to sleep out.

72
00:06:13,906 --> 00:06:17,466
I guess I'd rather take a walk out here

73
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:20,266
than sleep on the rattan chair.

74
00:06:20,266 --> 00:06:22,146
You can't walk all night.

75
00:06:29,346 --> 00:06:30,226
Then...

76
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:35,107
- How about...
- No.

77
00:06:35,747 --> 00:06:38,706
I'm not trying to sleep in your room.

78
00:06:39,507 --> 00:06:40,947
Don't get me wrong.

79
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:45,947
I'm not sleepy yet. I can walk with you.

80
00:06:49,987 --> 00:06:53,264
It's a long shore.

81
00:06:53,648 --> 00:06:56,906
Maybe we can walk until dawn
and see the sunrise.

82
00:07:00,026 --> 00:07:03,346
You're getting slower. Are you tired?

83
00:07:05,747 --> 00:07:08,906
Maybe it's because of the ascending.
I am a bit tired.

84
00:07:08,906 --> 00:07:11,667
Let's sit here for a break.

85
00:07:12,706 --> 00:07:13,346
Okay.

86
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:24,947
Actually, I enjoy talking to you.

87
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:29,987
Me too.

88
00:07:35,466 --> 00:07:37,386
So let's talk more.

89
00:07:39,826 --> 00:07:41,226
Sure. About what?

90
00:07:43,226 --> 00:07:44,867
About how you started the business.

91
00:07:46,146 --> 00:07:48,747
How I started the business.

92
00:07:51,386 --> 00:07:54,146
Well, when I was a kid,

93
00:07:54,146 --> 00:07:57,466
I was a troublemaker
and never studied, you know?

94
00:07:57,667 --> 00:08:03,667
Then I met Mo Qingcheng
and Feng Yasong after I graduated.

95
00:08:03,667 --> 00:08:07,386
I thought I shouldn't be left behind.

96
00:08:07,947 --> 00:08:10,747
So I worked hard to start the business.

97
00:08:12,067 --> 00:08:15,067
Come to think of it,
it's important to have good friends.

98
00:08:15,667 --> 00:08:19,466
A good influence keeps you motivated.

99
00:08:20,026 --> 00:08:23,187
- Yeah, that's me and Sheng.
- Right?

100
00:08:24,547 --> 00:08:30,466
Thanks to my buddies, I started
my business relatively smoothly.

101
00:08:31,427 --> 00:08:33,267
I guess I made it.

102
00:08:51,106 --> 00:08:55,626
So how did you
break up with your girlfriend?

103
00:09:04,826 --> 00:09:09,866
It was tiring to start the business
and I didn't have time for her.

104
00:09:10,427 --> 00:09:13,706
We slowly lost passion and broke up.

105
00:09:14,947 --> 00:09:15,787
Peacefully.

106
00:09:19,826 --> 00:09:20,826
Who brought it up?

107
00:09:22,947 --> 00:09:23,586
She did.

108
00:09:27,106 --> 00:09:29,667
Didn't you try to get her back?

109
00:09:32,027 --> 00:09:35,307
No, I think love has to be mutual.

110
00:09:36,547 --> 00:09:39,280
It takes two people
to have a relationship, after all.

111
00:09:40,304 --> 00:09:45,027
One-sided love doesn't lead anywhere.

112
00:09:47,466 --> 00:09:51,626
I agree that love should be mutual.

113
00:09:55,787 --> 00:09:57,226
Everybody needs feedback.

114
00:10:17,586 --> 00:10:19,067
Well, that's it.

115
00:10:19,826 --> 00:10:22,387
Let's keep walking.
It's getting cold sitting here, right?

116
00:10:23,307 --> 00:10:24,307
- Let's go then.
- Alright.

117
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:25,787
Let's go.

118
00:10:28,706 --> 00:10:32,706
Let's talk about you. Any plans?

119
00:10:34,106 --> 00:10:38,387
I want to get my postgraduate degree
and find a job I like.

120
00:10:39,307 --> 00:10:42,947
Hopefully, I can find someone I like
who also likes me.

121
00:11:31,947 --> 00:11:33,907
I actually slept here the whole night.

122
00:11:40,106 --> 00:11:41,106
Where is Xiaoxing?

123
00:11:57,826 --> 00:11:59,667
I deserve a massage, okay?

124
00:12:01,506 --> 00:12:01,986
Morning.

125
00:12:03,746 --> 00:12:05,947
I'll go upstairs to wash up.

126
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:19,267
You're finally back.

127
00:12:23,746 --> 00:12:25,307
Juemei slept here last night?

128
00:12:26,672 --> 00:12:27,760
Of course not.

129
00:12:28,624 --> 00:12:32,746
You ditched me for your boyfriend.
I stayed up all night. I'm so sleepy.

130
00:12:33,027 --> 00:12:34,586
You stayed up all night?

131
00:12:35,947 --> 00:12:37,547
Not only that,

132
00:12:38,787 --> 00:12:40,307
we went

133
00:12:42,106 --> 00:12:45,626
for a walk until dawn.

134
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:48,547
I was about to head back,

135
00:12:48,706 --> 00:12:52,027
but Mr. Mo texted Juemei that

136
00:12:52,147 --> 00:12:55,626
his wife had fallen asleep
and that he should sleep out.

137
00:12:55,746 --> 00:13:00,866
Where could he go?
So I walked with him all night.

138
00:13:00,986 --> 00:13:07,667
I can't invite him over for the night.
I have to be discreet.

139
00:13:12,986 --> 00:13:15,187
My legs are sore. Massage them.

140
00:13:17,027 --> 00:13:21,187
So Juemei was very decent
and didn't ask to share your bed.

141
00:13:23,147 --> 00:13:26,267
H-He is very decent.

142
00:13:28,787 --> 00:13:30,067
It's only 6:00. Let me sleep more.

143
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:38,307
Tell me what you did.

144
00:13:40,187 --> 00:13:42,907
Nothing. I was sleepy.

145
00:13:43,027 --> 00:13:46,147
You took a nap in the afternoon
but I only slept for ten minutes.

146
00:13:47,826 --> 00:13:49,168
So I fell asleep.

147
00:13:50,226 --> 00:13:50,947
That's it?

148
00:13:53,947 --> 00:13:56,307
Gu Sheng, you're so insensitive.

149
00:13:58,106 --> 00:13:58,787
Sleep.

150
00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:09,547
You should massage my legs, okay?
I walked the whole night.

151
00:14:11,106 --> 00:14:12,387
Don't you want to say something?

152
00:14:15,106 --> 00:14:18,226
Stop smiling. What a surprise.

153
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:21,147
You favor your girlfriend
over your buddies.

154
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:28,866
Think about it from another aspect.
I was creating opportunities for you.

155
00:14:29,936 --> 00:14:32,706
Creating opportunities? What for?

156
00:14:40,866 --> 00:14:45,226
- You think too much, okay?
- Yeah?

157
00:14:50,547 --> 00:14:55,466
But even if I'm interested,
I can't just sleep over at her place.

158
00:14:58,027 --> 00:15:01,106
Don't you know that we're just friends?

159
00:15:02,427 --> 00:15:03,226
I knew it.

160
00:15:04,346 --> 00:15:05,826
You're a decent guy.

161
00:15:07,626 --> 00:15:12,746
But you talked the whole night. You must
have learned more about each other.

162
00:15:22,147 --> 00:15:27,547
Mo Qingcheng, you're playing
tricks on me, huh? Just wait.

163
00:15:29,706 --> 00:15:30,147
Just wait.

164
00:15:32,947 --> 00:15:34,427
You have to be grateful.

165
